Analyze Flight Data: Visualization Project¶

Sarah Griggs¶

Table of Contents¶

  • Introduction
  • Part I - Initial Data Investigation & Cleaning
  • Part II - Explanatory Analysis

Introduction¶

This analysis will look at flight data from a period of 5 years, 2004 through 2008, to determine if there are patterns in delays change over time intervals.
This analysis is particularily interested in questions revolving around flight delays. Questions Explored are as follows:

  1. How are flight delays associated with years?
    1a. Do some years have more delays than others?
    1b. Does total delays as a percentage of total flights align with total delays per year?
    1c. Do certain types of delays contribute more to the yearly delay total than others?
  2. How are filght delays associated with day of week?
  3. How are flight delays associated with month of year?
  4. How are flight delays in total distributed among carriers?
    4a. Do total delays per flight carrier change as years progress?

Part I - Initial Data Investigation & Cleaning¶

Cleaning and an intital exploration of the data was preformed. The data was read in as 5 separtate data frames and then appeneded into a master. A datetime variable was created from the 3 columns, year, month, and day. This date time variable allows for easier reads of correlations. An additional boolean delay variable was created in order to indicate ifa delay was present at all. Last, individual delay booleans were created for each type of delay so that we could analyze these occurances as aggregates instead of minute amounts.
